    "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds dataclass-like OOP features to the `@aggregate` decorator, as discussed in #8781:\n\n- **Field inheritance**: child aggregates inherit parent fields via MRO resolution\n- **Default values**: fields with defaults can be omitted from constructor; defaults propagate through inheritance\n- **`aggregate_replace()`**: creates a copy of an aggregate instance with specified fields replaced (like `dataclasses.replace()`)\n- **Python 3.14 compat**: excludes `__annotate__` from aggregate member copying (same fix as #9529)\n- **Post-construction immutability**: `__setattr__` rejects mutation after `__init__` returns; users construct modified copies via `aggregate_replace`\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe current `@aggregate` decorator only reads `cls.__annotations__` — it does not resolve annotations from parent aggregate classes, support default field values, or functional updates. This limits composability when building layered Triton abstractions.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- `_resolve_aggregate_fields()`: walks the MRO in reverse order, collecting annotations and defaults from classes marked `__triton_aggregate__ = True` (filtering out infrastructure bases like `base_value`)\n- Defaults stored as `__aggregate_defaults__` on the processed class so child aggregates can inherit them\n- Member-copying loop now skips aggregate infrastructure methods (`__new__`, `__setattr__`, `_flatten_ir`, etc.) to prevent parent aggregate internals from overriding child closure-based implementations\n- `__annotate__` (Python 3.14+) excluded from member copying and hash computation\n- `aggregate_replace()` added as a standalone function in `triton.language` and re-exported in `gluon.language`\n- `__setattr__` lockdown via `_aggregate_init_complete` flag — accepts writes during `__init__`, rejects them after construction (matches `dataclasses(frozen=True)`)\n\n## Validation\n\nValidated on NVIDIA DGX Spark (SM121a / GB10) against a from-source build of `libtriton.so` matching the working tree.\n\n- Full `test_frontend.py`: 50/50 pass\n- 21 aggregate-tagged tests pass\n\nNew tests:\n- `test_aggregate_field_inheritance` — basic child inherits parent fields\n- `test_aggregate_multilevel_inheritance` — grandparent → parent → child\n- `test_aggregate_field_inheritance_with_methods` — inherited methods work with inherited fields\n- `test_aggregate_default_values` — explicit and omitted defaults\n- `test_aggregate_inherited_defaults` — child inherits default values from parent\n- `test_aggregate_default_value_auto_wrapped` — raw-int defaults auto-wrap to `tl.constexpr`\n- `test_aggregate_replace` / `test_aggregate_replace_invalid_field` / `test_aggregate_replace_non_aggregate`\n- `test_aggregate_post_construction_immutable` — `__setattr__` lockdown after construction\n- `test_aggregate_inheritance_ir` / `test_aggregate_inherited_method_ir` / `test_aggregate_replace_ir` — IR-level checks via `@filecheck_test`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Reproduce limitations on main\n- [x] All existing `test_frontend.py` tests pass\n- [x] New aggregate OOP tests pass\n- [x] IR-level checks for inheritance / inherited methods / `aggregate_replace`\n- [x] `__setattr__` lockdown blocks post-construction mutation; existing `@triton.jit` attribute-assignment rejection tests still pass\n\nContributed by Second Nature Computing (https://joinsecondnature.com)",
