      "merge_method": "squash",
      "commit_title": "[Language] Add field inheritance, defaults, and aggregate_replace to @aggregate (#9572)",
      "commit_message": "## Summary\n\nAdds dataclass-like OOP features to the `@aggregate` decorator, as\ndiscussed in #8781:\n\n- **Field inheritance**: child aggregates inherit parent fields via MRO\nresolution\n- **Default values**: fields with defaults can be omitted from\nconstructor; defaults propagate through inheritance\n- **`aggregate_replace()`**: creates a copy of an aggregate instance\nwith specified fields replaced (like `dataclasses.replace()`)\n- **Python 3.14 compat**: excludes `__annotate__` from aggregate member\ncopying (same fix as #9529)\n- **Post-construction immutability**: `__setattr__` rejects mutation\nafter `__init__` returns; users construct modified copies via\n`aggregate_replace`\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe current `@aggregate` decorator only reads `cls.__annotations__` — it\ndoes not resolve annotations from parent aggregate classes, support\ndefault field values, or functional updates. This limits composability\nwhen building layered Triton abstractions.\n\n## Implementation\n\n- `_resolve_aggregate_fields()`: walks the MRO in reverse order,\ncollecting annotations and defaults from classes marked\n`__triton_aggregate__ = True` (filtering out infrastructure bases like\n`base_value`)\n- Defaults stored as `__aggregate_defaults__` on the processed class so\nchild aggregates can inherit them\n- Member-copying loop now skips aggregate infrastructure methods\n(`__new__`, `__setattr__`, `_flatten_ir`, etc.) to prevent parent\naggregate internals from overriding child closure-based implementations\n- `__annotate__` (Python 3.14+) excluded from member copying and hash\ncomputation\n- `aggregate_replace()` added as a standalone function in\n`triton.language` and re-exported in `gluon.language`\n- `__setattr__` lockdown via `_aggregate_init_complete` flag — accepts\nwrites during `__init__`, rejects them after construction (matches\n`dataclasses(frozen=True)`)\n\n## Validation\n\nValidated on NVIDIA DGX Spark (SM121a / GB10) against a from-source\nbuild of `libtriton.so` matching the working tree.\n\n- Full `test_frontend.py`: 50/50 pass\n- 21 aggregate-tagged tests pass\n\nNew tests:\n- `test_aggregate_field_inheritance` — basic child inherits parent\nfields\n- `test_aggregate_multilevel_inheritance` — grandparent → parent → child\n- `test_aggregate_field_inheritance_with_methods` — inherited methods\nwork with inherited fields\n- `test_aggregate_default_values` — explicit and omitted defaults\n- `test_aggregate_inherited_defaults` — child inherits default values\nfrom parent\n- `test_aggregate_default_value_auto_wrapped` — raw-int defaults\nauto-wrap to `tl.constexpr`\n- `test_aggregate_replace` / `test_aggregate_replace_invalid_field` /\n`test_aggregate_replace_non_aggregate`\n- `test_aggregate_post_construction_immutable` — `__setattr__` lockdown\nafter construction\n- `test_aggregate_inheritance_ir` / `test_aggregate_inherited_method_ir`\n/ `test_aggregate_replace_ir` — IR-level checks via `@filecheck_test`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Reproduce limitations on main\n- [x] All existing `test_frontend.py` tests pass\n- [x] New aggregate OOP tests pass\n- [x] IR-level checks for inheritance / inherited methods /\n`aggregate_replace`\n- [x] `__setattr__` lockdown blocks post-construction mutation; existing\n`@triton.jit` attribute-assignment rejection tests still pass\n\nContributed by Second Nature Computing (https://joinsecondnature.com)\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Peter Bell <peterbell10@openai.com>"
    },
